                "minimum": "<strong>Minimum:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>OS:</strong> XP Service Pack 3<br></li><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Dual Core Processor<br></li><li><strong>Memory:</strong> 1 GB RAM<br></li><li><strong>Graphics:</strong> DirectX10-capable graphics card<br></li><li><strong>DirectX:</strong> Version 10<br></li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 160 MB available space<br></li><li><strong>Sound Card:</strong> DirectX compatible<br></li><li><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> Uses the XNA Framework HiDef profile, which means it will run on any graphics card that is compatible with DirectX 10 or higher, and some but not all DirectX 9c ones.  PLEASE NOTE: having a version of DirectX installed on your PC is not the same thing as having a graphics card that supports it!  If in doubt play the demo.</li></ul>",
